Package gw.api.modules.rest.framework.v1.updater.handler

Interface PropertyArrayUpdateHandler

public interface PropertyArrayUpdateHandler
Interface for classes that can be used as an array property update handler. An array handler is a class that can be specified for the "handler" attribute in the "items" object for the updater of a schema array property, and defines how items in that array are updated.

  • Method Details

    • configure

      void configure(HandlerConfig config, JsonUpdaterPropertyItems updaterPropertyItems, ConfigurationErrorReporter errorReporter)
      This method is called during compilation of the updater. Implement this method to define any validation/setup logic that should occur for the handler to work correctly.
      Parameters:
      config - configuration object representing the representing the attributes of the handler (the attributes of the updater property that are not part of the "items" spec)
      updaterPropertyItems - the array "items" object on which this handler is defined
      errorReporter - reporter on which to add errors, if any

    • applyUpdate

      void applyUpdate(String jsonKey, List<?> jsonValue, ObjectUpdateContext context)
      This method is called to update the associated schema array property. Implement this method to define how the array should be updated.
      Parameters:
      jsonKey - the name of the property containing the items being updated
      jsonValue - the list of target objects to which the array property is being updated
      context - context object containing the state of the update operation
